    "content": "<html>\n<head>\n    <title>Greedy Algorithm Demo</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n        }\n        #result {\n            font-size: 24px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            margin-bottom: 20px;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Greedy Algorithm Demo</h1>\n    <p>Greedy Algorithms are a type of algorithmic problem-solving strategy that involves making the locally optimal choice at each step in a sequence in order to make a globally optimal solution. This is often contrasted with the \"happier\" algorithm, which makes a solution that is good for all possible next moves.</p>\n    <h2>Example: Coin Change Problem</h2>\n    <p>Given a set of coins and a target amount, find the fewest number of coins needed to reach the target amount.</p>\n    <div id=\"result\"></div>\n    <script>\n        function coinChange(coins, target) {\n            let dp = new Array(target + 1).fill(Infinity);\n            dp[0] = 0;\n\n            for (let coin of coins) {\n                for (let i = coin; i <= target; i++) {\n                    dp[i] = Math.min(dp[i], dp[i - coin] + 1);\n                }\n            }\n\n            if (dp[target] === Infinity) {\n                return \"No solution\";\n            } else {\n                return dp[target];\n            }\n        }\n\n        let coins = [1, 2, 5];\n        let target = 11;\n        console.log(coinChange(coins, target));  // Output: 3\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
